parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The self-adjustment of rearview mirrors can cause distraction and obstruction of the driver's view, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The left and/or right rearview mirrors adjust randomly on their own
and may continue to do so repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning power side view mirrors can cause a distraction while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when changing lanes.
symptoms: The power side view mirrors move on their own
adjusting to different positions without command

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic panel can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to safety issues and inconvenience.
symptoms: the battery runs dead when the vehicle is not operated daily
and the electronic panel fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The passenger airbag fails to deploy in a crash
despite the vehicle being involved in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clockspring assembly can cause the horn and cruise control to become inoperable, and the air bag warning light to illuminate, which can lead to a lack of safety features in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The horn and cruise control are inoperable
the air bag warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and seatbelt can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the passenger may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The passenger's side airbag fails to deploy
the shoulder strap of the seatbelt fails to restrain the passenger
resulting in injuries such as head trauma and neck injuries.
